<i>So Santa hired Clyde on a consulting basis.</i>

1584
01:44:31,015 --> 01:44:33,017
Good. Very good.

1585
01:44:36,562 --> 01:44:40,148
Oh, it's a nice sweater, Clyde.
Real nice sweater.

1586
01:44:40,316 --> 01:44:44,816
NARRATOR: <i>Clyde's efficiency ensured that
the North Pole never fell behind again.</i>

1587
01:44:44,987 --> 01:44:48,365
<i>Even with every kid getting a present.</i>

1588
01:44:48,741 --> 01:44:53,241
<i>Willie and Charlene found out
that kindred spirits and soul mates...</i>

1589
01:44:53,454 --> 01:44:56,748
<i>often come in all shapes and sizes.</i>

1590
01:44:58,292 --> 01:45:01,920
<i>And Bob and Linda finally got e-mail.</i>

1591
01:45:02,087 --> 01:45:06,382
Linda, where are all the new orders?

1592
01:45:06,550 --> 01:45:10,011
I e-mailed you five minutes ago.

1593
01:45:10,179 --> 01:45:14,308
Please, do not use
all caps all the time, okay?

1594
01:45:14,475 --> 01:45:17,728
- Yeah, but...
- Not everything is that important.

1595
01:45:18,395 --> 01:45:19,646
Love you.

1596
01:45:20,147 --> 01:45:21,398
Love you back.

1597
01:45:21,565 --> 01:45:22,983
[CHATTERING LOUDLY]

1598
01:45:23,150 --> 01:45:24,901
You're jumping around like animals.

1599
01:45:25,194 --> 01:45:27,738
What are you doing? Stop.
What do you got your hat on...?

1600
01:45:27,905 --> 01:45:30,157
You don't have a video.
Wear your hat like a man.

1601
01:45:30,324 --> 01:45:32,451
Turn your hat around.
Put your hat on straight.

1602
01:45:32,618 --> 01:45:34,745
You wear it like this to block the sun.

1603
01:45:34,912 --> 01:45:36,747
When you're eating, take your hats off.

1604
01:45:36,914 --> 01:45:38,665
BOY: Yeah.
- She's right. Show respect.

1605
01:45:38,833 --> 01:45:42,086
Take off your hat. Don't forget "man"
is also in the word "manners."

1606
01:45:42,253 --> 01:45:44,922
Bring it in for a team chant here.
Ready? On three.

1607
01:45:45,089 --> 01:45:47,591
One, two, three, kill them!

1608
01:45:47,925 --> 01:45:51,261
NARRATOR:
<i>Fred never stopped watching over Slam.</i>

1609
01:45:51,428 --> 01:45:52,595
[CHATTERING]

1610
01:45:52,763 --> 01:45:54,681
MAN: Ah. SLAM: Whoa!

1611
01:45:54,849 --> 01:45:59,349
NARRATOR: <i>And by the next Christmas,
Slam had a family of his own.</i>

1612
01:46:00,312 --> 01:46:04,399
VOICES [ON TV]:
<i>Three, two, one, happy New Year!</i>

1613
01:46:04,692 --> 01:46:09,113
NARRATOR: <i>And Santa Claus finally got
the one present he always wanted.</i>

1614
01:46:09,280 --> 01:46:10,364
<i>He got his brother back.</i>

1615
01:46:10,531 --> 01:46:14,284
I'm not letting go. I got you
in a death grip. I'm not letting go. Aah!

1616
01:46:14,451 --> 01:46:17,412
FRED: Get out there.
- Look! Slimming down. Citrus fruits.

1617
01:46:17,580 --> 01:46:18,747
Get out there, big guy.

1618
01:46:18,914 --> 01:46:20,332
Bit more fancy, you know.

1619
01:46:20,499 --> 01:46:23,043
NICK: Wanda, excuse me.
Mind if I take her away for a second?

1620
01:46:23,210 --> 01:46:26,046
Oh, yeah, go right ahead.

1621
01:46:26,213 --> 01:46:28,381
Come here, Dad.
It's just you and me now.

1622
01:46:28,632 --> 01:46:30,467
NARRATOR:
<i>But as I told you before...</i>

1623
01:46:30,634 --> 01:46:33,970
<i>this is the story
of a boy named Fred.</i>

1624
01:46:34,138 --> 01:46:37,432
I just love Wanda. I mean, she's
a little bit above your station.

1625
01:46:37,600 --> 01:46:40,853
So I thought maybe you should just
sort of clean up your act, you know?

1626
01:46:41,020 --> 01:46:44,565
Have a great new wardrobe to start off
the new year. You're a Claus.

1627
01:46:44,773 --> 01:46:47,484
Get out there. You know,
look at your dad. He's so dapper.

1628
01:46:47,651 --> 01:46:49,778
Don't do it to me.
I'm trying to be positive.

1629
01:46:49,945 --> 01:46:54,445
Oh, but I'm positive too. I'm positive
I'm right. You need a new wardrobe.

1630
01:46:54,658 --> 01:46:55,784
Okay.

1631
01:46:56,076 --> 01:46:58,161
- Happy New Year to you, Mom.
- Happy New Year.

1632
01:46:58,329 --> 01:47:00,998
- I love you.
- I love you too.

1633
01:47:01,624 --> 01:47:03,083
NICK: That's more like it.

1634
01:47:03,250 --> 01:47:05,252
ANNETTE: Ooh.
NICK: How about that move?

1635
01:47:28,359 --> 01:47:31,320
[CHIRPING]

